procedures.name: Blood Draw
procedures.label: Venipuncture
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, pregnancy, and other laboratory assessments.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour pooled collection for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples to measure copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: Complete physical examination including cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems. Symptom-driven physical examinations may also be performed.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Oral Administration of Study Intervention
procedures.label: Drug Administration
procedures.description: Oral administration of ALXN1840 tablets once daily.

procedures.name: Medical History and Demographics Collection
procedures.label: History Collection
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, Wilson disease history, prior treatments, and demographic information.

procedures.name: Height, Weight, and BMI Measurement
procedures.label: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.description: Measurement of participant height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring, detection, and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannulation
procedures.description: Placement of an intravenous cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

code.decode: Introduction of needle or intracatheter, vein

procedures.name: Neurological Assessment
procedures.label: Neuro Assessment
procedures.description: Regular monitoring for neurologic adverse events and neurological dysfunction.

procedures.name: Informed Consent
procedures.label: Informed Consent
procedures.description: Process of obtaining and documenting informed consent from study participants.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure and Heart Rate Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device used to assess blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula placed in a vein to allow for repeated blood draws while minimizing needle sticks.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Laboratory equipment used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
